abstract: Many young people across the globe are experiencing high levels of economic threat, leading to substantial psychological distress. Two experiments examine the causal role of economic threat on distress through the experimental manipulation of economic threat. Furthermore, the curvilinear relationship between perceptions of control and distress during economic threat is also investigated.
